did.unittitle: Yale School of Drama photographs and posters

repository.corpname: Yale University. Department of Manuscripts and Archives

did.abstract: The materials consist of photographs, posters, and renderings of set designs and contact sheets documenting Yale School of Drama productions, including performances at the Yale Repertory Theatre, events, and individuals.

odd.head: General note
odd.p: Forms part of Yale Record Group 22-H (YRG 22-H), Photographs, audio-visual materials, and memorabilia documenting the Yale School of Drama.

accessrestrict.head: Conditions Governing Access
accessrestrict.p: The materials are open for research.

prefercite.head: Preferred Citation
prefercite.p: Yale School of Drama Photographs and Posters (RU 397). Manuscripts and Archives, Yale University Library.

arrangement.head: Arrangement
arrangement.p: The pictures are arranged by accession.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: The materials consist of photographs, posters, and renderings of set designs and contact sheets documenting Yale School of Drama productions, including performances at the Yale Repertory Theatre, events, and individuals..

userestrict.head: Conditions Governing Use
userestrict.p: Copyright for materials authored or otherwise produced as official business of Yale University is retained by Yale University. Copyright status for other collection materials is unknown.
